      "source": [
        "# A collection of >=10 Python code snippets (strings). Replace or extend as needed.\n",
        "code_snippets = [\n",
        "    # 1\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "def fib(n):\n",
        "    if n <= 1:\n",
        "        return n\n",
        "    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 2\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "class Stack:\n",
        "    def __init__(self):\n",
        "        self.items = []\n",
        "    def push(self, x):\n",
        "        self.items.append(x)\n",
        "    def pop(self):\n",
        "        return self.items.pop()\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 3\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "import math\n",
        "def is_prime(n):\n",
        "    if n < 2: return False\n",
        "    for i in range(2, int(math.sqrt(n))+1):\n",
        "        if n % i == 0:\n",
        "            return False\n",
        "    return True\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 4\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "from functools import lru_cache\n",
        "@lru_cache(maxsize=None)\n",
        "def ways(n):\n",
        "    if n<=1: return 1\n",
        "    return ways(n-1) + ways(n-2)\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 5\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "def quicksort(arr):\n",
        "    if len(arr) <= 1:\n",
        "        return arr\n",
        "    pivot = arr[len(arr)//2]\n",
        "    left = [x for x in arr if x < pivot]\n",
        "    mid = [x for x in arr if x == pivot]\n",
        "    right = [x for x in arr if x > pivot]\n",
        "    return quicksort(left) + mid + quicksort(right)\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 6\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "async def fetch(session, url):\n",
        "    async with session.get(url) as resp:\n",
        "        return await resp.text()\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 7\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "def flatten(lst):\n",
        "    return [x for sub in lst for x in sub]\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 8\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "class Node:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, val, left=None, right=None):\n",
        "        self.val = val\n",
        "        self.left = left\n",
        "        self.right = right\n",
        "\n",
        "def inorder(root):\n",
        "    if root:\n",
        "        inorder(root.left)\n",
        "        print(root.val)\n",
        "        inorder(root.right)\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 9\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "def binary_search(arr, target):\n",
        "    l, r = 0, len(arr)-1\n",
        "    while l <= r:\n",
        "        m = (l + r)//2\n",
        "        if arr[m] == target:\n",
        "            return m\n",
        "        elif arr[m] < target:\n",
        "            l = m + 1\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            r = m - 1\n",
        "    return -1\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 10\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "import requests\n",
        "\n",
        "def download(url, dest):\n",
        "    r = requests.get(url)\n",
        "    with open(dest, 'wb') as f:\n",
        "        f.write(r.content)\n",
        "\"\"\",\n",
        "    # 11 (extra)\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "def decorator_example(func):\n",
        "    def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):\n",
        "        print('Before')\n",
        "        result = func(*args, **kwargs)\n",
        "        print('After')\n",
        "        return result\n",
        "    return wrapper\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "len(code_snippets)\n"
      ]

      "source": [
        "def extract_ast_features(code_str):\n",
        "    tree = ast.parse(code_str)\n",
        "    funcs = []\n",
        "    classes = []\n",
        "    imports = []\n",
        "    patterns = {\n",
        "        \"list_comprehension\": False,\n",
        "        \"decorator\": False,\n",
        "        \"recursion\": False,\n",
        "        \"async\": False\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    # gather function & class names and other features\n",
        "    for node in ast.walk(tree):\n",
        "        if isinstance(node, ast.FunctionDef):\n",
        "            funcs.append(node.name)\n",
        "            if node.decorator_list:\n",
        "                patterns[\"decorator\"] = True\n",
        "            # detect recursion: function calling itself\n",
        "            for sub in ast.walk(node):\n",
        "                if isinstance(sub, ast.Call) and isinstance(sub.func, ast.Name):\n",
        "                    if sub.func.id == node.name:\n",
        "                        patterns[\"recursion\"] = True\n",
        "        if isinstance(node, ast.ClassDef):\n",
        "            classes.append(node.name)\n",
        "        if isinstance(node, (ast.Import, ast.ImportFrom)):\n",
        "            if isinstance(node, ast.Import):\n",
        "                for n in node.names:\n",
        "                    imports.append(n.name)\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                module = node.module if node.module else \"\"\n",
        "                for n in node.names:\n",
        "                    imports.append(f\"{module}.{n.name}\")\n",
        "        if isinstance(node, ast.ListComp):\n",
        "            patterns[\"list_comprehension\"] = True\n",
        "        if isinstance(node, ast.AsyncFunctionDef):\n",
        "            patterns[\"async\"] = True\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"functions\": funcs,\n",
        "        \"classes\": classes,\n",
        "        \"imports\": sorted(set(imports)),\n",
        "        \"patterns\": patterns\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test\n",
        "for i, code in enumerate(code_snippets[:3], 1):\n",
        "    print(i, extract_ast_features(code))\n"
      ]
    },

        "import token as py_token_const\n",
        "\n",
        "def python_tokenize(code_str):\n",
        "    tokens = []\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        reader = io.BytesIO(code_str.encode('utf-8')).readline\n",
        "        for tok in py_tokenize.tokenize(reader):\n",
        "            # skip enc/ENDMARKER/NEWLINE that are less informative\n",
        "            if tok.type in (py_token_const.ENCODING, py_token_const.ENDMARKER, py_token_const.NL):\n",
        "                continue\n",
        "            tokens.append((py_token_const.tok_name[tok.type], tok.string))\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        tokens.append((\"TOKENIZE_ERROR\", str(e)))\n",
        "    return tokens\n",

      "source": [
        "# Pretrained models from sentence-transformers (embeddings)\n",
        "model_names = {\n",
        "    \"MiniLM\": \"sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2\",\n",
        "    \"DistilRoBERTa\": \"sentence-transformers/all-distilroberta-v1\",\n",
        "    \"MPNet\": \"sentence-transformers/all-mpnet-base-v2\"\n",
        "}\n",
        "models = {}\n",
        "for k,v in model_names.items():\n",
        "    print(f\"Loading {k} -> {v} ...\")\n",
        "    models[k] = SentenceTransformer(v)\n",
        "print(\"Loaded models:\", list(models.keys()))\n"
      ]

      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "functions: fib | patterns: recursion\n",
            "\n",
            "def fib(n):\n",
            "    if n <= 1:\n",
            "        return n\n",
            "    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create short \"textualized\" representations to send to embedding models.\n",
        "# We'll combine code + AST-derived summaries so models see both code and structure.\n",
        "reprs = []\n",
        "for row in rows:\n",
        "    summary = []\n",
        "    if row[\"functions\"]:\n",
        "        summary.append(\"functions: \" + \", \".join(row[\"functions\"]))\n",
        "    if row[\"classes\"]:\n",
        "        summary.append(\"classes: \" + \", \".join(row[\"classes\"]))\n",
        "    if row[\"imports\"]:\n",
        "        summary.append(\"imports: \" + \", \".join(row[\"imports\"]))\n",
        "    patt = [k for k,v in row[\"patterns\"].items() if v]\n",
        "    if patt:\n",
        "        summary.append(\"patterns: \" + \", \".join(patt))\n",
        "    text_repr = \" | \".join(summary) + \"\\n\\n\" + row[\"code\"]\n",
        "    reprs.append(text_repr)\n",
        "# Show first example\n",
        "print(reprs[0][:400])\n"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "sim_matrices = {}\n",
        "for name, embs in embeddings.items():\n",
        "    sim = cosine_similarity(embs)\n",
        "    sim_matrices[name] = sim\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create a summary DataFrame of average pairwise similarity per model\n",
        "summary_rows = []\n",
        "for name, sim in sim_matrices.items():\n",
        "    # ignore diagonal by subtracting eye\n",
        "    n = sim.shape[0]\n",
        "    avg_sim = (sim.sum() - n) / (n*(n-1))\n",
        "    summary_rows.append({\"model\": name, \"avg_pairwise_cosine\": float(avg_sim)})\n",
        "summary_df = pd.DataFrame(summary_rows)\n",
        "display(summary_df)\n"
      ]

      "source": [
        "def plot_2d(emb, title):\n",
        "    # PCA then t-SNE on PCA-reduced to 50 dims for t-SNE stability\n",
        "    # Adjusted n_components to be at most the number of samples as well\n",
        "    pca = PCA(n_components=min(50, emb.shape[1], emb.shape[0]))\n",
        "    emb_pca = pca.fit_transform(emb)\n",
        "    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=5, n_iter=1500, random_state=42, init='pca')\n",
        "    emb_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(emb_pca)\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))\n",
        "    for i, txt in enumerate(df.id):\n",
        "        plt.scatter(emb_tsne[i,0], emb_tsne[i,1])\n",
        "        plt.text(emb_tsne[i,0]+0.5, emb_tsne[i,1]+0.5, str(txt), fontsize=9)\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"t-SNE 1\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"t-SNE 2\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True)\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "for name, emb in embeddings.items():\n",
        "    print(\"Plotting\", name)\n",
        "    plot_2d(emb, name + \" t-SNE (after PCA)\")"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "# We'll compare pairwise similarities between model pairs\n",
        "pairs = []\n",
        "n = len(reprs)\n",
        "for i in range(n):\n",
        "    for j in range(i+1, n):\n",
        "        pairs.append((i,j))\n",
        "data = []\n",
        "for (i,j) in pairs:\n",
        "    row = {\"i\": i, \"j\": j}\n",
        "    for name, emb in embeddings.items():\n",
        "        row[f\"sim_{name}\"] = float(cosine_similarity(emb[[i]], emb[[j]])[0,0])\n",
        "    data.append(row)\n",
        "sim_df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
        "sim_df.head()\n"
      ]
    },

        "## Example Observations (you should expand in README)\n",
        "- MPNet embeddings show generally higher overall cosine similarity among short code snippets than DistilRoBERTa on this small dataset.\n",
        "- MiniLM is efficient and produces compact vectors; it may cluster structurally similar snippets (e.g., recursive functions) closer.\n",
        "- Visual inspection (t-SNE) helps to see which snippets cluster (e.g., IO-heavy code vs. algorithmic computations).\n",
        "- Limitations: small dataset, not fine-tuned for code (using general sentence models). For code-specific embeddings consider CodeBERT / CodeT5 / GraphCodeBERT.\n",
